Adjust racks to middle and top positions and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Place @butter{2%tbsp} in a #small bowl{} and bring to room temperature.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}; place in 1 #oven-ready aluminum tray{1} (divide chicken between 2 trays for 4).

Brush top of each chicken cutlet with @honey Dijon dressing{1/2%tbsp} (save the rest for serving). Sprinkle with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}. Crush @crispy fried onions{1} in their package, then sprinkle on top of cheese, pressing to adhere.

Roast on middle rack until chicken is cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}. (You'll add more to the oven after ~{5%minutes}.)

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Add @green beans{6%ounce} to remaining #oven-ready aluminum tray{1}; add @water{1%tbsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, divide green beans between remaining 2 trays; add 1 TBSP water per tray.) Cover completely with #foil{}.

Once chicken has roasted 5 minutes, add green beans to top rack. Roast until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

When chicken is almost done, combine @softened butter{}(remaining 1 tbsp) in #bowl{} with @garlic powder{1%tsp} to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Halve and toast @ciabatta bread{1}. Spread cut sides with garlic butter. Cut each half on a diagonal.

Carefully uncover green beans and drain any liquid; toss with @plain butter{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide chicken, green beans, and garlic bread between plates. Serve with @honey Dijon dressing{1%tbsp} on the side. Enjoy your meal without worrying about any cleanup from cooking!

> Crunchy chicken is always a recipe for success. The chicken's swiped with a tangy-sweet honey Dijon dressing, then sprinkled with melty Monterey Jack and crispy fried onions. Once baked, the crust turns golden brown while the meat stays juicy and tender. Winner winner chicken dinner!